#### Replication Link Watchdog

Each node runs a watchdog (`repl-watchdog.sh`) that pings each peer's
point-to-point IP every 10 seconds. If a peer is unreachable for 30 seconds,
the watchdog brings down the local interface to force traffic onto the fallback
route via the third node. When the peer recovers, the watchdog brings the
interface back up automatically.

This converts asymmetric link failures (one end down, other end up) into
symmetric failures that the dual-metric routing handles correctly.

- Deployed by: `configure-node-network.sh`
- Timer: `repl-watchdog.timer` (every 10s)
- Logs: `journalctl -u repl-watchdog`
- State: `/run/repl-watchdog/`
{%- endif %}

