### Cluster Formation

After network configuration is verified, form the Proxmox cluster:

```bash
framework/scripts/form-cluster.sh
```

Preview the commands without executing:
```bash
framework/scripts/form-cluster.sh --dry-run
```

Cluster name: **{{ cluster_name }}**
{% if cluster.name == 'AUTO' %}
(Auto-derived from domain `{{ domain }}`. To change, set `cluster.name`
in `site/config.yaml`.)
{% endif %}

> **Note:** `form-cluster.sh` pre-distributes SSH keys between all nodes before
> running any `pvecm` commands. This is the same key exchange that `pvecm` would
> perform during join, done in advance to enable `--use_ssh` (non-interactive
> join). The keys become part of the permanent cluster auth fabric at
> `/etc/pve/priv/authorized_keys`.

The following commands are executed automatically by `form-cluster.sh`.
They are shown for reference only — **do not run them manually.**

**Create cluster on {{ nodes[0].name }}:**
```bash
ssh root@{{ nodes[0].mgmt_ip }} \
{%- if has_replication_network and nodes[0].repl_ip is defined %}
  pvecm create {{ cluster_name }} \
    --link0 {{ nodes[0].repl_ip }} \
    --link1 {{ nodes[0].mgmt_ip }}
{%- else %}
  pvecm create {{ cluster_name }}
{%- endif %}
```

{%- for node in nodes[1:] %}

**Join {{ node.name }}:**
```bash
ssh root@{{ node.mgmt_ip }} \
{%- if has_replication_network and node.repl_ip is defined %}
  pvecm add {{ nodes[0].mgmt_ip }} --use_ssh \
    --fingerprint <FINGERPRINT> \
    --link0 {{ node.repl_ip }} \
    --link1 {{ node.mgmt_ip }}
{%- else %}
  pvecm add {{ nodes[0].mgmt_ip }} --use_ssh \
    --fingerprint <FINGERPRINT>
{%- endif %}
```
{%- endfor %}

