### Snippet Storage

After cluster formation, enable cloud-init snippet storage on the cluster.
OpenTofu uploads cloud-init user-data and meta-data as snippets to each node.

```bash
framework/scripts/configure-storage.sh
```

Preview what will be changed without modifying:
```bash
framework/scripts/configure-storage.sh --dry-run
```

This modifies `/etc/pve/storage.cfg` (cluster-synced) to add `snippets` to the
`local` storage content types, and ensures `/var/lib/vz/snippets/` exists on
each node.

> **Image file extensions:** Proxmox's `local` storage (ISO content type) only
> recognizes files with `.iso` or `.img` extensions. If you upload a `.raw` or
> `.qcow2` file directly, Proxmox will silently ignore it — it won't appear in
> the UI or be available for VM disk import. The `upload-image.sh` script handles
> this by using the `.img` extension automatically.

**Verify:**
```bash
framework/scripts/configure-storage.sh --verify
```
- [ ] `ssh root@{{ nodes[0].mgmt_ip }} "grep snippets /etc/pve/storage.cfg"` shows `snippets` in the content line
{%- for node in nodes %}
- [ ] {{ node.name }}: `ssh root@{{ node.mgmt_ip }} "ls -d /var/lib/vz/snippets"` succeeds
{%- endfor %}
